values:
KK, so an update of the last 10 minutes:

I emailed James and asked him to talk to me before he sorts out accommodation for next year, cos he might be able to have my room

I emailed JP (my almost sorta step dad) and asked him if I can go to Australia with him

Let's see how this goes...

I am BORED! It's pretty shitty timing all around. For the last few weeks, Marks been up for going out and having some drinks but I was broke, and now since I've been paid he's been panicking about his end of year exam (6 days to go) and is too busy. I even feel guilty when I go downstairs for coffee and talk to him. I think I distract him. I dunno. Solitude does keraaaazy things to teh Djem. BORED! I keep bouncing between trying to fight back tears and giggling hysterically at practically nothing. I saw Ciaran briefly on the way home from work. Theres a possibility that I may have called him "Fag" in front of his mother...

I decided, since I have to move out 4 hours earlier than initially planned and Moving Day is in a weeks time, to actually try and pack. Well, not pack as such since I only have one suitcase here, but at least sort out a) which stuff is being thrown, b) which stuff is being sent home and c) which stuff I actually deem worthy enough to keep close to me next year. Funness. Do I keep the cylinder of blue (or is it green? Who knows!) goo? My solar powered dancing flower? Do I really *need* a magic 8 ball? After having a rather long and sadly loud debate with myself, I now have a slowly deflatnig Nemo at my feet. I dont *need* him, I dont... However, I must keep the dancing Cleopatra hamster that sings Walk Like An Egyptian, it's clearly an essential... 

So, I say I "decided to pack". Well, I have a bag of books that I dont need or that I borrowed from mum and JP, a half-filled suitcase, multiple bin bags full of various shit that for the life of me I dont recall how I accumulated it all. Currently, I'm saving Nuklear Power and Kimonos Townhouse webcomics strip by strip for later perusal (dont know how long I'll be net-less for - a better use of my time might be looking into internet packages for the new place... meh.) and watching Blues Brothers. I might as well watch it with the sound down, I'm lip-synching the words as it is... I swear I know every line. This is sad.

The new printers pretty shiny. I'm getting a load of psych journal articles off so I can file em away, maybe take em to work and occupy my mind on my break. Its not a bad printer, considering how cheap it was n all. A bit grey, not really black, not sharp, and the machine makes this strange ... juddering sorta sound when its finished, sounds like its about to explode at any moment. I keep unconsciously leaning towards the right and ducking slightly... I'm sure it'll grow on me. Maybe I should name it, help along the precious bonding process between man and machine.

Are you the police? 
No ma'am. We're musicians.

Friday Five: The sun goes down alone

1. Have any road trips planned?
Nah. Unless you count me and mum driving back to Notts? Odds are she'll be too tired to talk, and I'll be forced to endure the latest travesty that is Billy Connolly on cd

2. What is out of your reach?
Happiness, seemingly. Sanity... The really nice Chicago Town pizzas in Tescos Extra - always on the top damned shelf!

3. Are you more likely to watch a sunset or the sun rise?
Personally I'd be more likely caught staring out the window at sunset, I dont like mornings, but stupid shift work means I'm generally walking to work around sunrise.

4. What night will you never forget?
The night nii-san slashed up his arm. Only me and him know the real story behind how it happened, and I intend on keeping it that way

5. Whats the last thing that made you scream?
Myself, and the sheer frustration that is my life



Altfriday5: Proud of the altfriday5, once again

1. What are you proud of about yourself?
I'll get back to you on that one

2. Tell us about one of your proudest moments
I know, I know... I was told that I wasn't allowed to do A Level Psychology cos I only got a C in Maths, and a B was "required". I nagged, and whined and threatened to go to college and leave sixth form. They eventually let me in the class. I was one of the two people who got an A. That was my first ever A. The head called me into his office at the end of the year and apologised, and told me how proud of me he was. That was a good day ^^

3. Who in your life are you proud of?
I dont feel like I have the right to be proud of anyone really. I guess James, Lisa - she'll still be that little girl with the skipping rope and the plaster on her knee to me, Jo obviously. She's doing so well for herself ^^

4. Pick one of the people from #3  and tell us about one of the proudest moments (when you felt a lot of pride in them)
I'm constantly impressed by nii-san, there is no one defining moment. The things he comes out, the things he has to deal with, the way he handles things. Everythings so hard, yet he still finds the time to make *me* of all people feel special, like I'm the only person in the room and he wants nothing more than to listen to what *I* have to say. He always tries his best when it comes to the people in his life (works a whole 'nother ball game... *imagine a Minnesota Maccy-G style drawl here*). I'm proud of him for being so strong and putting up with so much, without a word of complaint. I'm proud of his bravery and his capacity for forgiveness. And I'm proud to call him my best friend

5. No five today

Friday fiver: Trying to fit a rectangle into a ball.

1. When do you doubt yourself?
Generally, I dont doubt myself much without other people making me feel the need to. You know, when they give you *that* look... and your insides shrivel up and you rack your brain trying to think exactly what you might have done, said, wore etc to piss them off so much. Left to my own devices, there isn't much doubting. That is, of course, unless you count when I get into the depressive arc of my infradian cycle ^^

2. Who do you owe an apology?
Helen

3. When is the last time you felt embarrassed? 
The morning after the last night I went out and started wondering what on earth people would think of me now.

4. What do you ignore?
Personal boundaries, little red men, discussing important things with the one person besides me that they *actually* effect, counting calories of my choice of alcoholic beverage

5. Do you love yourself? 
At times, I dont *hate* myself ^^ Naw, I guess I'm ok with me really... 

Alternative Friday Fiver: Assets

1. What do you consider is your best "asset" physically? Why?
Er... my lips/smile. Thats what I've been complimented the most on (I disregard all comments given by drunken strangers in a dark room...). I have the same lips as my mum and I like that

2. What do you consider is your best "asset", personality-wise? Why?
I guess I'm very honest and open-minded, if you want an opinion or advice, or just someone to listen to you and give advice, I'm kinda good at that

3. Have you ever deliberately photographed your physical "assets" or had them photographed? Why or why not?
No, can't say I have. Thought about it maybe, but who would I show? Thanks to Nii-san and his 4chan obsession, I've seen what can happen when the wrong kinda people get hold of that sorta thing

4. Have you ever posted photos showing off your physical "assets"? Why or why not? If yes, who was able to see the photos (a select group, all your friends, anyone)?
[see above]

5. Whose assets would you most like to see a photo of?
Hmmm... RDA about 20 years ago. Bet he was stud...

If I sat outside would you come watch me wait?

would you promise not to get out of the way?

My first attack, I'll put a knife against your throat
and cut an inch for every time I lost my self-control
and you made me do the things I did at night when I got home

But I thought you'd change, but I realize that today, today

Evelyn, I know you lied. But I'll tell you that I'm alive for the first time
and I'm begging you to leave here now. I'm begging you to stay away from me.
I know you lied. I'll tell you that I'm alive for the first time
and I'm begging you to leave here now. I'm begging you to die painfully.

Oh, painfully...

So this brings us to the backup of my plan.
Maybe I'll just have to strangle you with my bare hands.

and occupy a shallow grave, as shallow as you are.

But I thought they'd change but things just stayed the same, the same

Dunno why, just heard this song and thought  "Fuck yeah". No idea who I had in mind at the time, it just, on some level, seemed appropriate... *shrugs*

 Anyway, Friday Fiver: So we're mad... 

1. Are you attracted to the naughty or the nice?
Nice is a shit adjective. Implies sickeningly perfect, and boring. I guess naughty-ish

2. Do you let your dirty laundry pile up?
HAH! I'm wearing yesterdays socks...

3. What's the last excuse you made?
"Sorry, I cant go out, I'm broke". Not really an excuse cos it's true (but I didn't wanna go anyway...)

4. Do you play it safe or do you take risks?
Probably play it safe. Sickeningly boring, thats me *grins*

5. Friday fill-in:
Let's go to the SGC and play golf through the gate.

I had an extremely crap morning, but I'm going to be an extremely petty backstabbing bitch and tell Lynda tomorrow exactly how late Owen was and exactly how much he pissed off and inconvenienced me and the store. He's a nice lad, fun to go out drinking with but the most self-centred unreliable TWAT I've ever had the misfortune to work with and I feel no shame in ratting him out to the boss cos it's NOT good enough. I got a week off next week, so I'll be heading down to the Job Centre etc, making a go at the job hunt thing. 

Anyway, after a shitty start and a lot of crying and feeling sorry for myself, I had a pretty nice afternoon. I came home to find Mark "working" and watching a Disney film, Alaska I think in the kitchen. So I watched a bit of that, and then went up the stairs with the intention of tidying or writing up my cv or making some notes or doing something even remotely productive. But then, I decided I wanted some tea, so I went downstairs, where Mark and now Janek as well were watching Parent Trap. So I had to stay, obviously. And Parent Trap was swiftly followed by Father of the Bride II. I love bank holidays and the shitty films that fill up the day. It was nice, in a strange way. Kinda familiar and comfortable. Mark sat on one couch reading and making notes, me on the other with my su doku book, both drinking luke warm tea. It reminded me of home. We'd always watch tv together when we had free time as opposed to anything else - we considered it less effort than real family bonding, cos although we were technically in the same room doing the same thing, it involved no actual communication or interactions whatsoever ^^

So, overall, not a bad day. James has gone out with Lowri now, I decided to stay in with some cans, cos I'm not in the mood for feeling inferior and guilty about the fact that I have to work in a chemist to pay my rent. I should possibly re-evaluate my definition of "friend" cos I'm sure they're not sposed to make me feel the way the people I refer to as "friend" now do... Marks got some friend round, and I think he's a bit pissed cos said friend decided to mention that going out for a few/a nights worth of drinks is outta the question as he's broke. Mark's birthday party is this Sat in St Helens, I'm kinda looking forward to it. The party, not visiting St Helens for the first time, I've heard bad things...

Rose

Dont disturb the beast
The temperamental goat, the snail
While he's feeding on the rose
Stay frozen compromise what I will, I am

Bend around the wind
Be silently thrown about again
I'm treading so soft and lightly
Compromising my will, I am
I am, I will, so no longer
Will I lay down, play dead, play your doe
In the headlights locked down and terrified
Your deer in the headlights
Shut down and horrified
When push comes to pull comes to shove
Comes to step around this self-destructive dance
That never would have ended
 Til I rose, I roared aloud here
'I will, I am'

I am, I will so no longer will I lay down
Play dead, play this beat-down, gun-shy, martyr (pitiful)
I ROSE, I ROARED, I WILL, I AM

A groan of tedium escapes me, startling the fearful
Is this a test?
It has to be. Otherwise I can't go on
Draining patience, drain vitality
This paranoid, paralysed vampire act's a little old

But I'm still right here, giving blood and keeping faith. And I'm still right here

I'm gonna wait it out

If there were no rewards to reap,
No loving embrace to see me through this tedious path I've chosen here,
I certainly would have walked away by now
I'm gonna wait it out

If there were no desire to heal
The damanged and broken met along this tedious path I've chosen here
I certainly would've walked away by now
I still may. And I still may
Be patient

I must keep reminding myself of this

If there were no rewards to reap,
No loving embrace to see me through this tedious path I've chosen here,
I certainly would've walked away by now

I'm gonna wait it out
I'm gonna wait it out
Gonna wait it out


Parabol

So familiar and overwhelmingly warm
This one, this form I hold now.
Embracing you, this reality here,
This one, this form I hold now, so
Wide eyed and hopeful.Wide eyed and hopefully wild.

We barely remember what came before this precious moment,
Choosing to be here right now. 
Hold on, stay inside...This body holding me, reminding me that I am not alone in
This body makes me feel eternal. All this pain is an illusion.


Parabola

We barely remember who or what came before this precious moment,
We are choosing to be here right now. Hold on, stay inside...
This holy reality, this holy experience. Choosing to be here in...
This body. This body holding me. Be my reminder here that I am not alone in
This body, this body holding me, feeling eternal all this pain is an illusion.

Alive

This holy reality, in this holy experience. 
Choosing to be here in...This body. 
This body holding me. Be my reminder here that I am not alone in
This body, this body holding me, feeling eternal all this pain is an illusion...
Of what it means to be alive

Swirling round with this familiar parable.
Spinning, weaving round each new experience.
Recognize this as a holy gift and celebrate this chance to be alive and breathing
Chance to be alive and breathing

This body holding me reminds me of my own mortality. 
Embrace this moment. 
Remember we are eternal all this pain is an illusion.


Reflection

I find that I can see a light at the end down 
Beneath my self-indulgent pitiful hole
Defeated I concede and move closer
I may find comfort hereI may find peace within the emptiness
How pitiful...
It's calling me, it's calling me, it's calling me, it's calling me

And in my darkest moment, faetal and weeping
The moon tells me your secrets, my confidant
As full and bright as I am
The light is not my own and
A million light reflections pass over me

The source is bright and endless 
She resuscitates the hopeless
Without her we are lifeless satellites drifting

And as I pull my head out
I am without one doubt
Dont wanna be down here, soothing my narcissism
I must crucify ego, before its far too late
And pray the light lifts me out 
Before I pine away, before I pine away, before I pine away, before I pine away

So crucify ego before its far too late
And leave behind this place so negative and blind and cynical
And you will come to find, that we are all one mind
Imagining all conceivable
Just let the light touch you and let the words spill thorough
Just let them pass right through, bringing out our hope and reason.


Lateralus

I embrace my desire to feel the rhythm, to feel connected enough to step aside and weep like a widow, to feel inspired, to fathom the power, to witness the beauty, to bathe in the fountain, to swing on the spiral of our divinity and still be a human.

I can't believe it. I NEVER get lie-ins. Ever. And what do I do instead of enjoy them? Wake up at 4.30 in the morning shit scared about my money situation and still pissed from last night. I'm such an idiot... And now I can't get back to sleep even though I haven't been awake that long.

Things aren't that much worse than they were yesterday. I just remembered that they're lowering my overdraft soon-ish, of course, all my paperworks being sent home and mum is being her usual helpful self and just leaving them unopened in my room - a room btw that I have entered less than 3 times in the last 2 years. As soon as we move out from this dump I'll get my post re-directed to teh new house - there seems to be no point doing it now when I move out next month. But til then, I have no fucking idea what my bank account is doing unattented. *panic panic panic* Ok, all better....

Delta Goodrem. Very nice voice. Stupid songs. Well, I only have 3 of them. Not Me, Not I. Very pretty. She's like, "do what you want, i dont care, i can do better anyway, im not gonna cry just cos you break up with me, who cares anyway?". Then, Lost Without You. "If we ever break up i dont know what id do, im lost without you". The fact that she released both songs from the same album, takes all the positive meaning away from the first song, cos she clearly doesn't mean it and would sing any song thrown at her purely for the money. I mean, if a pop stars job is to provide some sort of role model for kids, then she fails based on her inconsistency. Random thought that has actually been putting me in a bad mood lately. Gah...

So, my plan of action (at 4.53am on a fucking bank holiday Sunday... *grumble*) - I'm not too sure. I have a hot chocolate, I've put my washing on, charged my phone, gone to the toilet, I've got a notepad so I can at least work out for definate how shit my money is. If I just buy a pack of bottles of water and multipack of crisps then I'll save shitloads at work - I spend a fortune there on food. If I include breakfast in my daily routine then I wont be so hungry at work and wont have to eat so much anyway. See, there are ways to save money. Main one I'm thinking of is the beer. I dont even enjoy it anymore, and I feel fat. So, that'll have to stop. So, I'll work out money, and maybe (try to) complete some sudokus. Cant believe I missed out on those so long, James only just explained em to me, and like... wow! I'm so tired

Feeling a bit better now I guess. Got a phone call from Gem earlier, she's back in Liv on Tue, and staying til Fri so I think we're meeting up on Wed to sort the house stuff out and catch up. That should be nice. 

Apparently Ciaran and James were pretending to be ninjas last night and stole a sofa. Huh...

I love Sundays! I would have enjoyed my lie in more if it wasn't rudely interupted by Libby and Friend coming in at 8am, slamming the door, giggling hysterically, running up the stairs, still giggling, then back out the door, slamming it in their wake. Gah! It's a Sunday! What right do they have to giggle anyway...?

Met up with Helen and the usual breakfast gang and went to the Pilgrim cos the Cambo is closed this week. James and Ciaran had the breakfasts and were finished in 20 minutes, but Mark, Helen and I ordered the three course Sunday lunch so we took considerably longer. Damn, that was some mighty fine chocolate cake ^^

Now and always 

1. What was on your mind yesterday?
Money, probably. Pay day soon

2. What is on your mind today?
Money, still. Or lack thereof. Pay day tomorrow. Woo...? 

3. Do you like bonfires?
Yeah. Gettin all wrapped up so I can meet my friends in some huge park covered in orange leaves, when it's so cold that your breath mists in front of your face, but you dont care cos you have a toffee apple and a big fire to look at and lots of friends feeling exactly the same

4. Do you believe in the paranormal?
Dunno, haven't any experience, but I wont completely deny its existence. Yet...

5. Can you swim? 
Not well

Funky funky club on Fairfax Avenue

1. What do you obsess about?
EVERYTHING!

2. What do you do for a living?
Sell my soul, dignity, every ounce of pride I ever thought I possessed, for a few measly quid that I will inevitably waste. 

3. Where do you call home?
I don't really call anywhere home. I could up and leave tomorrow and it wouldn't faze me much. I've done it a million times before, and I could do it again

4. Have you lived up to your parents' expectations?
Do I care that I may or may not have lived up to my parents expectations?

5. Are we more likely to find you in a coffee bar or a nightclub? 
Nightclub I guess. Coffee makes me feel sick



 Why does it always seem like there's some huge drama always going on in my life? Maybe cos I over-react to everything... I saw my mum on Sunday and her and John Paul are breaking up. I have no idea how to feel about this. I thought it was fine, but all yesterday I just felt like bursting into tears, the family I thought would always be there for me has fallen apart, and again I'm left with no one. I suggested me coming home to live next year, but mum made it very clear that I wouldn't be welcome. She wants to enjoy her new found singledom. Can't blame her. Quite scary that my safety net has been so callously taken away though. 

She told me in the car when she came to pick me up. I guess I was a bit shocked, but what can I do? I asked all the usual nice questions, "are you ok, are you happy with this, when did this happen, why did this happen,who's getting the house, could you afford the house on your own". Apparently Laura and Vicky got all hysterical and started crying and shit. I'm not sure if I didn't react that way merely cos of my amazingly mature and understanding attitude, or maybe its cos I feel so detatched from the lot of them that I don't consider that it will affect me at all. Probably the latter. I promised to email mum with times I'm off so we can have one last family get together, I haven't yet. She promised to email me to let me know when she was getting back off holiday and when she'd be likely to come up to Liverpool next. She hasn't yet. It's a bit of a joke really... I did speak to JP on the phone. He seems relieved that I'm not an emotional hysterical wreck who blames him for hurting my mummy. I guess part of me figures, why bother show how upset I am to these guys, they dont need to have to worry about me on top of everything else. And I've been through this whole song and dance before, I know what to say and how to act to make them feel better, and I guess out of the five of us - mum, JP, Laura, Vicky and me - mum and JP are the ones that need our comfort. They dont need Laura and Vicky crying at them. Laura lives in Warwick for crying out loud, she barely tolerates JP's presence when she's forced to be in the same room as him, why the hell was she worked up anyway? Probably cos Vicky was and her crying meant she was getting all the attention. I'm so glad I didn't go home and find out with the two of em. Don't think I coulda coped.

Solitude: the state of being alone, separated from other people, whether considered as a welcome freedom from disturbance or as an unhappy loneliness

That pretty much sums it up. I've been alone for a long time and now everyone's back and it's weird. The fridge is full. There are funny smells coming from the toilet that I didn't make. The shower isn't always free when I want it. I've seen Libby once, she's probably gone to Hannah and Louise's. I saw Mark briefly but now the front door is unbolted so he's probably gone to visit his "good friend" Jo (hah!). James is on the phone to Hannah, they're already arguing. And I'm sat here. Like I have been all holiday. It shouldn't bother me and it's not much, it's just... well, why does nothing ever turn out like I plan? Don't get me wrong, I like my alone time, lots. But I may have over-dosed recently. I'm really glad that they're all back but I've been acting like my old stupid self again and arguing with everyone. I'm just not used to people all around, all the time, again. It'll change. When James gets off the phone, we're gonna maybe have some food and watch another few episodes of Ebichu: The House-Keeping Hamster, which is hysterical semi-hentai with a talking hamster. Pure genius-ness. And then all will be well

I had a really good day all in all. We went to the Pilgrim for breakfast, and then had a wander in town. Went to the comic shops and I got me the latest NewType so I can ogle all the shiny newness that must be added to my "To DL" list. Got the new NIN album and an old one that I haven't heard before. Also got a mousemat that makes both my mice go haywire. Typical. But its so pretty :/ It was a fun day despite Ciaran being his usual charming self. I went out with him on Fri night and had a great time, and a really good talk with him. Tomorrow I supposedly start a week's transfer work in the photographic department in Clayton Square. So that should be... interesting. And if everything goes well and i dont fuck up then I'll start to look for a new job while I still have a firm grip on the new found confidene thing. Kewl...

Oooh, I forgot how good Phantom of the Opera is. I've only ever seen the film, it'd be great to watch it as a play. Need to have some very talented people though...

So, much to everyones amazement, I've decided I want a new job. It's kinda like the whole telling your best friend you think their boyfriends a useless twat and she's better off without him. She isn't gonna believe you unless she wants you, unless she sees it for herself. It takes one moment of blinding clarity and a rush of common sense. I could very stay at Boots. But I'm bored. I can do better, I deserve better. And, now I want better. Next week, I'm working in the photographics lab in Clayton Square. If that goes well, if the "me trying to make friends and be social (yes I know I can be when I try)" works then I will have the confidence to sign up with Adeco and will start job hunting. Properly. "So this has pissed me off for a while. Like, hm, twenty years.

How did Dick become short for Richard? I could take Rick without raising an eyebrow. I liken it unto tolerating lichen -- ohhh, see what I did there?

We can examine this Dick/Richard thing scientifically, but all it will do is shatter your every confidence in all empirical knowledge. Watch:

Obviously, there's a pattern at work here. The D in Dick didn't come out of nowhere. This isn't some kind of goddamn Moon-D. It's right there at the end of Richard.

So, okay. Step one. Take the last letter of your original name and make it the first letter.

That explains that.

Now what about that K? That, well, that is a Moon-K.

So now our second step is to replace the fourth letter of the original name with a K for no reason at all. Fine.

Therefore, according to the logic of the Richard-to-Dick transformation, Nrik is obviously short for Brian.

One addition to the system: if you don't have at least four letters in your name, you have no business searching for a shorter version of your name. So stop pouting."

Let's see. I haven't really gone out since every one left for easter. I kept meaning to go out with Lowri but we kept missing each other, and cancelling. Apparently, she's been out every single night with her lab, but just neglected to mention to me. Well, I occasionally get some beers from Tescos, but I'm learning to replace my alcohol cravings with tea. Equally addictive and bad for you, but I think its a step in the right direction. Mark came back on Friday, I can't remember why. Apparently he and Jo have broken up (again). For good this time. He seems quite resigned to it. They're gonna be friends. And I wont comment further as this changes nothing. NOTHING. So, we went out to the Cambo for "one quick pint", and 5 or 6 drinks and two pubs later, he left to go home. I wasn't planning on going out at all over the weekend. Well, Lowri text and said she was meeting some friends in Sefton Park on Sat afternoon, so I had to tag along. When I saw Lowri by her door, my first thought was "Who's that tool standing next to her?" It was Ciaran. Just wearing a white shirt and sunglasses, which I never EVER thought I'd witness. He looked pretty good though. Antonio came along and we met up with Tim, French Paul, Erwan, Val and his gf and daughter (Teh Cuteness!). From there we decided to gatecrash Martinas bbq, and I really wish I'd just left to go home with Ciaran and Antonio. Lowri was being bizarrely quiet and I didn't speak a word to anyone besides her. I just sat in the corner and drank. I took 4 cans with me, I wasn't really planning on getting drunk. It was the Polish pear flavoured vodka shots that must've done it. Apparently I fell over a few times, and walked into a wall. Though knocked over candles, I think that was funnier. Much. 

Anyway, I went home early and promised to text Lowri when I was home safe. Oops. I was pissed ok? I was running on autopilot, I didn't even get changed, I just slumped on my bed and passed out. I didn't think she'd mind. Anyway... I woke up at 6.15am to find 9 missed calls, 2 irate messages and a pile of pebbles on my windowsill. Woops... She still wont let me forget it. She should know that I can sleep through anything after first year and Charlie and Petes epic fights and window-smashings, that I only ever heard about the morning after, despite the fact that my room was closest to hers. Meh...

So, Sunday, I vowed not to drink at all. Me and Lowri and Cazza went to the Pilgrim for breakfast. They have hash-browns so yay, but the beans were cold and the sausages were nasty. I cant wait til the Cambridge starts its Sunday breakfasts again. They're scrum. Anyway, I didn't even drink at breakfast, that was how hungover I was! Marks friend Millers little brothers band were playing in Roadkill at 7 so I went with Lowri and Ciaran again, with the intension of having a "two pints max" limit. Well, before I knew it, Lowri and Ciaran had left me with an extremely pissed Mark, and then Gem came along. I couldn't be the only one not drinking now could I? It was a good night. They sell Space Invader crisps there, I'd forgotten how awesome they were! Maybe, it was the amount of alcohol in my system that made them taste that good... Whatever. They were tres yum at the time ^^

Not much else has happened. I work, I come home, I download anime, I watch tv, pretend to tidy my room. It's very lonely living on my own. I dont generally see anyone outside of work during the week. But Nii-san and the rest of the house come back this weekend, so cool.

Then I watched Brokeback Mountain and was actually *cringe* sobbing at the end, which coincidentally, was exactly the point when mum and Bev returned home. So, yeah, I scored loadsa Cool Points at home... 

Well, like I say, I got to see some films I'd been meaning to go out and see, I didn't check the tv paper early enough, cos apparently Cowboy Bebop was on scifi but I only discovered this half an hour AFTER it finished. Dammit... whenever I check there's never anything good.... Read some books, re-started Wheel of Time, half way through the China Mieville book which, while well-written, still hasn't gone anywhere yet... Disappointing, but I'll read it through cos James always raves about it. Also part way through Terry Pratchett Wintersmith and I started a book about Time Travel in Einsteins Universe. Did you know that if you travelled 500 light years away from earth at a speed of 99.995% of the speed of light and then came back at the same speed (another 500 light years), you would only age 10 years, but the earth would have aged 1000 years (or 10,000... I forget) The point is, time travel to the future is possible and has happened. Apparently some astronaut is a percentage of second younger than he would've been if he wasn't an astronaut. Not much, but y'know what they say about baby steps n all... That's a good book. I'll have to re-read and take notes, cos Maynard knows I wont remember anything this time next week.

I'm kinda bored. I'd have liked to go out, but ever since my two main drinking buddies have vacated the immediate area, Lowris decided that she's bored of the pub and wants to do other things like watch tv. I think my disgust at this idea speaks for itself.

I was just preparing to move to Liverpool actually. I was about to take my A Levels, I was living at home with mum and JP. Vicky and Laura had already moved out due to various circumstances. It was just the three of us. Mark and Lisa (and Jo of course!) were my best friends, and I couldn't imagine meeting anyone else who could compare to them. Not much really bores me, no matter what I'm doing (or supposed to be doing) or where I am, I can usually find something to entertain me - if not other people, or random objects to play with, I have quite an elaborate fantasy world that I can escape to when necessary ^^

Well, that depends who you ask. I can't dance to save my life, at least I dont think so. James thinks I have the potential to be a good guitar player cos I can hear a rhythm and repeat it, I understand them, I see blanks and lines in my head when I hear them. But I dunno how accurate he is...

Hmm... Anyone at this point! But no one in particular. It's sad, but there's no huge, overwhelmingly life-consuming crush at the minute. Always thought I'd have someone

So... Having one of those days y'know? I'm enjoying this loneliness, time to catch up on all the stuff that I want to, that I need to do. And that I've been planning on doing for a while. But the fact that Lowri isn't back, Ciarans more than likely to have headed home already, James is gone, Marks working and odds are Jo gets back soon, so he'll spend the evening with her and not in the pub with me... It's just a bit too lonely. But I like this. I know its only for a few weeks. Not even that, Lowri gets back tonight for crying out loud! But still, I'm starting to feel the way I used to. Oh, and I found that song that I adore, that every pub plays... Fast Car. It's beautiful and it makes me want to cry everytime I listened to it. I went to Tescos and bought some beers, cos it's a warm pretty day and I wanted to get out, but I'm not good at wondering aimlessly. If I have a task, I can walk anywhere, no matter how far, but if I haven't got an aim in mind, I cant make myself walk. Not enough beer to get me drunk anyway, I know how that hurts Mark, to see my misery displayed so blatantly, so hopelessly. I just felt like one. It's feeling a lot more summery now, I like summer. Despite all of the shit last year, last summer was brilliant. I really enjoyed it, more than I ever planned to. I'm looking forward to this one. 

Well, anyway, the combination of beer, loneliness and this damned beautiful song, I feel a bit depressed. But I'm not gonna wallow in it, I'm not gonna cry. If I refuse to take any pills, and I avoid my counselling appointments then I must do something for myself. That was the ultimatum I gave myself, and I'm damn well gonna live up to it. If I refuse everyone else's help, I've got to at least help myself. So, I'm watching random shitty programs that make me laugh, and I'm goin over my old psychology notes. Tomorrow I'll get a bank statement and figure out exactly how dismal my money situation is, and I'll start to plan, start to save. For  my birthday holiday with James and Lowri and for my Open Uni course. I'm looking forward to both. Both would make me feel like my life has more meaning, and pissing my life away in the meantime because I feel that I haven't actually got a life yet... well, thats just plain stupid. So, I have a plan, its vague and it may take years to set it all in motion, but I've always been patient with the things that matter to me. 

I'm gonna get back to my Green Wing marathon and Handbook of Jungian Psychology. And my beer, ofc ^^ Nite

I've had a really good week all in all. Wednesday I was on the early with a late the day after (and an assumed lie-in) so we went to the AJs (or the LDs as we may call it from now on :p ). It was initially me, James and Mark, but then Jenny came and sat with us, and with her cam Vicky, her bf and Tom. He is a sweet heart. Not attractive in a head-turning striking way, but in a cheeky cocky little swine sorta way. He was sweet. Shame him and me didn't last longer. But he's sorta with Jenny now (among many MANY others) and man is she a trap. I swear, she's a guy. She acts manlier than he does. And he's pretty manly... (Aerospace engineer, swimming champ, rifle club *sweat, drool*). Anyway, met up with them. It was nice to be in new (or techincally old... How about different?) company. I enjoyed it. Didn't stay long cos I was shattered and James went to meet his parents in their hotel. 

Work was, y'know, worky. Thursday I came home to find James sharing the last two of OUR burgers with Markus! Grrr... So, I had a baked potato and we all sat in the kitchen, chatting, Mark playing his guitar, all of us attempting the Times crossword. We did pretty damn well. I got, oh at least 2 clues all by myself. And 12 down came to me at work the next day - enchilada of course! Yesterday made the week though. It was great. I finished work earlyish, dl some yuri, the usual. James spent the afternoon with his parents. Me and Mark watched Neighbours and then James gave me a call, and invited me out to dinner with his parents. I love his parents, I wish they would adopt me! His mum has always been lovely, a really nice understanding caring woman. James's dad I've also really liked - he's very passionate about his job and he is very very funny and intelligent, but he also seemed quite wound up and tense. He was actually smiling and laughing - I swear I heard him giggle like a little girl at one point! It was so nice to see him so happy. We went to the Everyman cafe/restaurant thing - I had cajun salmon with 3 different salads and pastas and it really filled me up. The Merlot added to the atmosphere quite nicely too. As soon as James and his dad went to look at the dessert board, his mum started talking to me, probing, asking my opinion - as if I knew her son better than she. It was, a little sad in a sense that she needed to hear this sorta information from me, but flattering that she thinks I can answer her questions. She is so nice. I had a great evening - alcohol (always helps), good food and good company. Perfect :)

Today, I woke unnaturally early and helped James pack/sat on his desk and watched GitS SAC while he packed and then helped carry all his stuff to the car with his parents. And the rest of the day - I've done all my washing. Every last bit of it. Wootles. And I even hoovered the floor. My room looks deceptively tidy but thats cos everything that was previously on my floor is now on my bed. When I inevitably get too tired to play more computer games, I'll just throw it all back on the floor again before crawling into bed and tomorrow morning my room will once more be a mess. It's like the circle of life. I should learn to accept that I am never EVER going to have a tidy bedroom. 

Libby should be getting back this weekend - then I can talk to her about Malise moving in. Her and Mark's courses dont finish til Thur so I'll have some company for the first week of the hols at least. Janek doesnt leave til Wed. And Lowri should be getting back at some point tomorrow. I wont be lonely. And hey, I wouldn't mind if I was. I could catch up on my smut-fic reading, computer game playing and psychology note-taking. I quite like being on my own. I get to sing (and I use that term, very VERY loosely...) at the top of my lungs and no one complains. Well, only the neighbours but they dont count. Y'know I started watching Stargate from the beginning a few weeks back? I'm on the last episode of season 7. It's depressing how quickly I eat em up. I officially have no life. Or at least, a shitty one. Whatever...

I'm bored. So, I'm gonna either play Simon the Sorceror and lol to myself at the stupidity of the dialogue, breed Sim puppies (I WILL figure out how to do it!!) or assassinate some important people in the world of The Elder Scrolls. Decisions, decisions....

So, been a while huh? I really suck at this writing regularly thing, to which many of my friends from home can attest. Meh... I'm feeling ok atm, those stupid pills are finally working their way outta my system it seems. I'm still tired roughly 23 hours of the day, but when it comes to trying to get to sleep, it takes me a good 2 hours. Sleep is such a waste of time - there are so many more important things I'd rather spend my time on. Anyway, that and the food situation. Instead of being constantly hungry and constantly stuffing my face, now I feel hungry about once every 2 days or so, and thats painfully hungry at which point I'll eat and instantly feel sick. Dont get me wrong, I eat in between actually being hungry (mainly out of habit), but generally I dont feel hungry or full or sick. Well, every other day I do, for about an hour. It's great to feel like me again *confused smile* ...

Works not bad I spose. I hate the fact that the hours I'm most awake outta the day I waste in that place. I'm having much more fun with the people though, it's a real laugh at the minute. I've opened up a lot and they all seem to actually like me. Which is, y'know... nice ^^ Last week was heavenly cos Maureen was on holiday and Lynda was ill, so effectively we were boss-less for the whole 7 days. It was bliss. This week, Maureens making up for the lost time, by giving people stupidly inane and humiliating jobs, insulting people and coming up with new rules that surely go against our basic rights as human beings. Not only are we not allowed to blow our noses on the toilet paper (it's a waste of resources!) but now we're not even allowed the radiator on in the staff room when we're on our break - it might set the fire alarms off. I'm sorry... a radiator? Are you stupid woman? I mean, really... She has no fucking clue. She's just doing it to be mean. Plus, she must've hit the menopause by now, hot flushes and all, why would she want the heating on at work? Bitch...

What else? Oh yeah! My friend Malise might be moving in with us! We went to Southwell two summers ago, dug a few trenches, analysed some pottery shards, drew some pretty (complicated) diagrams, and of course, got pissed. Twas nice. Haven't really seen her much since, but she messaged me on facebook, and ouila! She's in need of a room, for now and possibly later, and the house I'm in now, as well as the one I'm moving into over summer, both have spare rooms. Fate, it must be. She's really nice, I think she's coming around tomorrow to view the house - that might put her off completely, it is such a shit hole. Might have to actually, clean it *shudder*

I was supposed to go to another counselling session today, but I bailed. I was really really not in the mood. I'm fine. I am god damn going to get better, I wont accept failure in this. I know who I want to be, what I want out of life and how to get it. So I'm working on that. I dont need some stupid bint asking probing questions about my childhood and parenting. I know it was shit, I dont want your sympathy or your judgement. Without that, I wouldn't be me, and (and I know this next statement may shock some people) I actually quite like me at the minute. I wouldn't change a thing, not for the world. I dont wanna go anymore. I'll be fine. I will

So, we went out after work to Bistro Jacques with James and had a really nice meal. I'm so stuffed, still. I love that place. Then we went to the Philharmonic for a quick drink and a chat. She seems to get along better with James than me but it was very nice to see her. She says I look well and all. I feel good. Better than I have in a long time. I'm glad she came up because I was more than a little annoyed that my mothers day weekend plans fell apart. She loved the Lilly Allen cd I got her and the card. It was a damn cute card: 



See the cuteness? ^^ It made me smile anyway
